5:
Three cheers for Diletta! Congrats
on beating your personal record for
most wins in a season!
6:
As both fellow fishermen and fans of
yours, we're so stinkin' proud of you!
8:
Yeah, yeah, I heard you the first
hundred times. Man, you guys don't
know when to quit.
11:
And three cheers to her trainers, too!
Stuff your faces to your hearts'
content.
14: Thank you. This food is very delicious.
17:
I still can't believe you guys rented
out a restaurant boat for this.
Doncha think you're going a bit
overboard?
20:
Gyahaha! It wasn't that expensive!
These waters have been overrun by
pirates lately, so they were
practically beggin' for customers.
23:
...And you didn't think to tell us about
the pirates?
26:
Come on, it's fiiine! Besides, if they
try to mess with us, we've got Diletta
on our side! We fishermen can hold
our own too!
28:
We'll be takin' this here ship, ya filthy
landlubbers!
38:
Hah-hah! Now give us all the grub
and booty you can find, or we'll
make you walk the plank!
43:
Hey, jerkwads! You've got a lotta
nerve interrupting our party like this!
45:
Who you callin' landlubbers?! We're
men of the sea just like you sorry lot!
Don't you dare look down on us
fishermen!
49:
W-well, blow me down. These
seadogs wanna fight! In that case,
give 'em a good showing, boys!
53:
Phew, I think that takes care of this
area...
57:
Now to find Diletta and Nimbus...
Perhaps they're at the bow of the
ship?
73:
Nngh! Didja think that would work on
me? I'll show yooouuu!
80:
You're doin' great, Diletta! Just keep
pilin' on the hits!
83:
Ah, so you guys finished up over on
your end of the boat, huh?
86:
Y-yeah. Uh... Care to explain what's
going on?
89:
Diletta's taking on the pirate captain
one-on-one. Before I knew it, they
had themselves an audience.
93:
Both camps have stopped their
quarrels and are fully absorbed in
the spectacle...
98:
This calls fer drastic measures!
Feast your eyes on this, lass! Pirate
Suplex Slam!
103:
Gah! P-pretty good for an old timer!
But guess what?
114:
Hehe, didja see that, boys? Looks like
I'm your champion!
123:
Good game, lass. You beat me fair 'n
square... But blimey, what a fight!
127:
Thanks, man. You weren't half bad
yourself.
129:
I haven't felt this good losin' since I
went up against Ardor the Masked...
Hell, he might be the only other
match I enjoyed!
137:
Pops?! So you're his kin! Of course,
we know him!
140: We're all huge fans of his!
146:
We had ourselves a wee spar back
in the day, and the crew and I were
hooked after that!
149:
Hate to admit it, but we haven't
been keepin' up with the sport since
he retired. I had no idea his
daughter was carryin' on the family
legacy!
151:
Don't know how I missed it. Your
styles match up perfectly!
155:
Tch. I ain't doing this to carry on his
legacy. I'm my own fighter!
165:
You bet your booty he was. But more
importantly, fightin' him was a riot.
168:
Gotcha... Then I guess I can let it
slide. Don't compare us ever again
though!
173:
E-excuse me, lass... Could we get yer
autograph?
176:
Get in line, ya sea dog! Cap'n gets
first dibs!
180:
These guys realize they're going to
jail, right?
184:
Okay, fine. I guess you've all earned
yourselves some autographs. I'll sign
your clothes, how's that sound?
194:
Ah, wait! Could you write "Ardor the
Masked II" under your name here?
199:
Who you think you're messing with,
huh?!
